From: Esod <psvita-port>
Subject: [PATCH] v_video: do not dereference missing credit font glyphs

`hu_stuff.c` (HU_LoadGraphics) sets `cred_font[i] = NULL` whenever the
`CRFNTxxx` lump for that character does not exist:

	if (W_CheckNumForName(buffer) == LUMPERROR)
		cred_font[i] = NULL;
	else
		cred_font[i] = (patch_t *)W_CachePatchName(buffer, PU_HUDGFX);

But both credit-font drawing routines only check that the character is
*within range* (CRED_FONTSTART..CRED_FONTEND), never that the glyph
actually exists, and then dereference the pointer:

	c = toupper(c) - CRED_FONTSTART;
	if (c < 0 || c >= CRED_FONTSIZE)
		{ ... skip ... }
	w = SHORT(cred_font[c]->width) * dupx;   /* <-- NULL deref */

The range check is not enough: '/' (0x2F), '+', '%', ':' and friends are
all inside '!'..'Z', and SRB2Kart's data has no glyph for them.

Vanilla credits happen to avoid those characters, so this never fires in
the stock game — it is a latent crash that hits the moment anyone adds a
credit line containing one. We hit it on the PS Vita port with a line
reading "PS Vita / PS TV Port": opening the credits menu was an instant
data abort (null pointer dereference) in V_CreditStringWidth.

Skip characters with no glyph, exactly as if they were out of range.
---
 src/v_video.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/src/v_video.c
+++ b/src/v_video.c
@@ -2083,8 +2083,11 @@ void V_DrawCreditString(fixed_t x, fixed_t y, INT32 option, const char *string)
 		}

 		c = toupper(c) - CRED_FONTSTART;
-		if (c < 0 || c >= CRED_FONTSIZE)
+		// Being in range does not mean the glyph exists: hu_stuff.c leaves
+		// cred_font[c] NULL when the CRFNTxxx lump is missing (e.g. '/').
+		if (c < 0 || c >= CRED_FONTSIZE || !cred_font[c])
 		{
 			cx += (16*dupx)<<FRACBITS;
 			continue;
 		}

@@ -2113,7 +2116,8 @@ INT32 V_CreditStringWidth(const char *string)
 	for (i = 0; i < strlen(string); i++)
 	{
 		c = toupper(string[i]) - CRED_FONTSTART;
-		if (c < 0 || c >= CRED_FONTSIZE)
+		// Same as V_DrawCreditString: a character in range may have no glyph.
+		if (c < 0 || c >= CRED_FONTSIZE || !cred_font[c])
 			w += 16;
 		else
 			w += SHORT(cred_font[c]->width);
